trans-unit.source: To register the app for push notifications through Apple Push Notification Service (APNS), you must create a new push certificate, App ID, and provisioning profile for the project on Apple's developer portal.
trans-unit.target: To register the app for push notifications through Apple Push Notification Service (APNS), you must create a new push certificate, App ID, and provisioning profile for the project on Apple's developer portal.

trans-unit.source: The App ID will contain the configuration settings that enable your app to send and receive push notifications.
trans-unit.target: The App ID will contain the configuration settings that enable your app to send and receive push notifications.

trans-unit.source: These settings will include the push notification certificate needed to authenticate with Apple Push Notification Service (APNS) when sending and receiving push notifications.
trans-unit.target: These settings will include the push notification certificate needed to authenticate with Apple Push Notification Service (APNS) when sending and receiving push notifications.

trans-unit.source: For more information on these concepts see the official [Apple Push Notification Service](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=272584) documentation.
trans-unit.target: For more information on these concepts see the official [Apple Push Notification Service](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=272584) documentation.

trans-unit.source: Generate the Certificate Signing Request file for the push certificate
trans-unit.target: Generate the Certificate Signing Request file for the push certificate

trans-unit.source: These steps walk you through creating the certificate signing request.
trans-unit.target: These steps walk you through creating the certificate signing request.

trans-unit.source: This will be used to generate a push certificate to be used with APNS.
trans-unit.target: This will be used to generate a push certificate to be used with APNS.

trans-unit.source: On your Mac, run the Keychain Access tool.
trans-unit.target: On your Mac, run the Keychain Access tool.

trans-unit.source: It can be opened from the **Utilities** folder or the **Other** folder on the launch pad.
trans-unit.target: It can be opened from the **Utilities** folder or the **Other** folder on the launch pad.

trans-unit.source: Click **Keychain Access**, expand **Certificate Assistant**, then click **Request a Certificate from a Certificate Authority...**.
trans-unit.target: Click **Keychain Access**, expand **Certificate Assistant**, then click **Request a Certificate from a Certificate Authority...**.

trans-unit.source: Select your **User Email Address** and **Common Name** , make sure that **Saved to disk** is selected, and then click **Continue**.
trans-unit.target: Select your **User Email Address** and **Common Name** , make sure that **Saved to disk** is selected, and then click **Continue**.

trans-unit.source: Leave the **CA Email Address** field blank as it is not required.
trans-unit.target: Leave the **CA Email Address** field blank as it is not required.

trans-unit.source: Type a name for the Certificate Signing Request (CSR) file in **Save As**, select the location in **Where**, then click **Save**.
trans-unit.target: Type a name for the Certificate Signing Request (CSR) file in **Save As**, select the location in **Where**, then click **Save**.

trans-unit.source: This saves the CSR file in the selected location; the default location is in the Desktop.
trans-unit.target: This saves the CSR file in the selected location; the default location is in the Desktop.

trans-unit.source: Remember the location chosen for this file.
trans-unit.target: Remember the location chosen for this file.

trans-unit.source: Register your app for push notifications
trans-unit.target: Register your app for push notifications

trans-unit.source: Create a new Explicit App ID for your application with Apple and also configure it for push notifications.
trans-unit.target: Create a new Explicit App ID for your application with Apple and also configure it for push notifications.

trans-unit.source: Navigate to the [iOS Provisioning Portal](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=272456) at the Apple Developer Center, log on with your Apple ID, click **Identifiers**, then click **App IDs**, and finally click on the **+** sign to register a new app.
trans-unit.target: Navigate to the [iOS Provisioning Portal](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=272456) at the Apple Developer Center, log on with your Apple ID, click **Identifiers**, then click **App IDs**, and finally click on the **+** sign to register a new app.

trans-unit.source: Update the following three fields for your new app and then click **Continue**:
trans-unit.target: Update the following three fields for your new app and then click **Continue**:

trans-unit.source: **Name**: Type a descriptive name for your app in the **Name** field in the **App ID Description** section.
trans-unit.target: **Name**: Type a descriptive name for your app in the **Name** field in the **App ID Description** section.

trans-unit.source: **Bundle Identifier**: Under the **Explicit App ID** section, enter a **Bundle Identifier** in the form `<Organization Identifier>.<Product Name>` as mentioned in the [App Distribution Guide](https://developer.apple.com/library/mac/documentation/IDEs/Conceptual/AppDistributionGuide/ConfiguringYourApp/ConfiguringYourApp.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40012582-CH28-SW8).
trans-unit.target: **Bundle Identifier**: Under the **Explicit App ID** section, enter a **Bundle Identifier** in the form `<Organization Identifier>.<Product Name>` as mentioned in the [App Distribution Guide](https://developer.apple.com/library/mac/documentation/IDEs/Conceptual/AppDistributionGuide/ConfiguringYourApp/ConfiguringYourApp.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40012582-CH28-SW8).

trans-unit.source: This must match what is also used in the XCode or Xamarin project for your app.
trans-unit.target: This must match what is also used in the XCode or Xamarin project for your app.

trans-unit.source: **Push Notifications**: Check the **Push Notifications** option in the **App Services** section, .
trans-unit.target: **Push Notifications**: Check the **Push Notifications** option in the **App Services** section, .

trans-unit.source: On the Confirm your App ID screen, review the setting and after you have verified them click **Submit**
trans-unit.target: On the Confirm your App ID screen, review the setting and after you have verified them click **Submit**

trans-unit.source: Once you have submitted the new App ID, you will see the **Registration complete** screen.
trans-unit.target: Once you have submitted the new App ID, you will see the **Registration complete** screen.

trans-unit.source: Click **Done**.
trans-unit.target: Click **Done**.

trans-unit.source: In the Developer Center, under App IDs, locate the app ID that you just created, and click on its row.
trans-unit.target: In the Developer Center, under App IDs, locate the app ID that you just created, and click on its row.

trans-unit.source: Clicking on the app ID row will display the app details.
trans-unit.target: Clicking on the app ID row will display the app details.

trans-unit.source: Click the **Edit** button at the bottom.
trans-unit.target: Click the **Edit** button at the bottom.

trans-unit.source: Scroll to the bottom of the screen, and click the **Create Certificate...** button under the section **Development Push SSL Certificate**.
trans-unit.target: Scroll to the bottom of the screen, and click the **Create Certificate...** button under the section **Development Push SSL Certificate**.

trans-unit.source: This will display the "Add iOS Certificate" assistant.
trans-unit.target: This will display the "Add iOS Certificate" assistant.

trans-unit.source: [AZURE.NOTE] This tutorial uses a development certificate.
trans-unit.target: [AZURE.NOTE] This tutorial uses a development certificate.

trans-unit.source: The same process is used when registering a production certificate.
trans-unit.target: The same process is used when registering a production certificate.

trans-unit.source: Just make sure that you use the same certificate type when sending notifications.
trans-unit.target: Just make sure that you use the same certificate type when sending notifications.

trans-unit.source: Click **Choose File**, browse to the location where you saved the CSR for your push certificate.
trans-unit.target: Click **Choose File**, browse to the location where you saved the CSR for your push certificate.

trans-unit.source: Then click **Generate**.
trans-unit.target: Then click **Generate**.

trans-unit.source: After the certificate is created by the portal, click the **Download** button.
trans-unit.target: After the certificate is created by the portal, click the **Download** button.

trans-unit.source: This downloads the signing certificate and saves it to your computer in your Downloads folder.
trans-unit.target: This downloads the signing certificate and saves it to your computer in your Downloads folder.

trans-unit.source: [AZURE.NOTE] By default, the downloaded file a development certificate is named **aps_development.cer**.
trans-unit.target: [AZURE.NOTE] By default, the downloaded file a development certificate is named **aps_development.cer**.

trans-unit.source: Double-click the downloaded push certificate **aps_development.cer**.
trans-unit.target: Double-click the downloaded push certificate **aps_development.cer**.

trans-unit.source: This installs the new certificate in the Keychain, as shown below:
trans-unit.target: This installs the new certificate in the Keychain, as shown below:

trans-unit.source: [AZURE.NOTE] The name in your certificate might be different, but it will be prefixed with **Apple Development iOS Push Services:**.
trans-unit.target: [AZURE.NOTE] The name in your certificate might be different, but it will be prefixed with **Apple Development iOS Push Services:**.

trans-unit.source: In Keychain Access, right-click the new push certificate that you just created in the **Certificates** category.
trans-unit.target: In Keychain Access, right-click the new push certificate that you just created in the **Certificates** category.

trans-unit.source: Click **Export**, name the file, select the **.p12** format, and then click **Save**.
trans-unit.target: Click **Export**, name the file, select the **.p12** format, and then click **Save**.

trans-unit.source: Remember the file name and location of the exported .p12 push certificate.
trans-unit.target: Remember the file name and location of the exported .p12 push certificate.

trans-unit.source: It will be used to enable authentication with APNS by uploading it on the Azure Classic Portal.
trans-unit.target: It will be used to enable authentication with APNS by uploading it on the Azure Classic Portal.

trans-unit.source: Create a provisioning profile for the app
trans-unit.target: Create a provisioning profile for the app

trans-unit.source: Back in the iOS Provisioning Portal, select **Provisioning Profiles**, select **All**, and then click the **+** button to create a new profile.
trans-unit.target: Back in the iOS Provisioning Portal, select **Provisioning Profiles**, select **All**, and then click the **+** button to create a new profile.

trans-unit.source: This launches the **Add iOS Provisiong Profile** Wizard
trans-unit.target: This launches the **Add iOS Provisiong Profile** Wizard

trans-unit.source: Select **iOS App Development** under **Development** as the provisiong profile type, and click **Continue**.
trans-unit.target: Select **iOS App Development** under **Development** as the provisiong profile type, and click **Continue**.

trans-unit.source: Next, select the app ID you just created from the **App ID** drop-down list, and click **Continue**
trans-unit.target: Next, select the app ID you just created from the **App ID** drop-down list, and click **Continue**

trans-unit.source: In the **Select certificates** screen, select your development certificate used for code signing, and click **Continue**.
trans-unit.target: In the **Select certificates** screen, select your development certificate used for code signing, and click **Continue**.

trans-unit.source: This is a signing certificate, not the push certificate you just created.
trans-unit.target: This is a signing certificate, not the push certificate you just created.

trans-unit.source: Next, select the **Devices** to use for testing, and click **Continue**
trans-unit.target: Next, select the **Devices** to use for testing, and click **Continue**

trans-unit.source: Finally, pick a name for the profile in **Profile Name**, click **Generate**.
trans-unit.target: Finally, pick a name for the profile in **Profile Name**, click **Generate**.
